title: recordbreaking
extract: record-breaking adjective [ before noun ] uk ​ /ˈrek.ɔːdˌbreɪ.kɪŋ/ us ​ /ˈrek.ɚdˌbreɪ.kɪŋ/ better, bigger, longer, etc. than anything else before: Company profits are rising and it looks as though this is going to be a record-breaking year. Successful (things or people)
